Mouthful Alert!!!: ( sorry in advance for this monster of a post- it’s good stuff though if you can stay with me 😂)

The reality is that high-quality, CLEAN, all natural caffeine ( from coffee beans ) has a TON of surprising benefits: 

1. May help lower your risk of type two diabetes. Coffee is jam-packed with phytochemicals that may act as antioxidants, anti-inflammatory compounds, insulin-sensitivity boosters and more. research is still on going, but there is a large body of evidence already to support.

2. Protects your ticker. As counterintuitive as it may seem, your go-to for kick�-starting the day �or powering� you through a sluggish afternoon has heart-healthy benefits. A review of three major studies published in “Circulation: Heart Failure” found that one serving of caffeine from coffee beans ( 85mgs a day) may reduce your risk for heart failure.

3. Boosts brain health. A long-term study published in 2021 in Frontiers in Aging Neuroscience,found that coffee-drinking participants with no memory impairments at the start of the study had a lower risk of developing mild cognitive impairment� —� which often precedes Alzheimer’s disease — or Alzheimer’s itself over the course of the 10-year study, compared with those who didn’t drink coffee. 

4. Improves your mood! ( for longer than you’d guess) Drinking coffee may reduce your risk of depression by �nearly one�-third, according to research from Harvard Medical School. The effect may be related to coffee’s anti-inflammatory properties. coffee has phytochemicals that feed the good bacteria in our guts. The good bacteria may produce or enhance other compounds that act on the brain and have beneficial effects on mood. 

And if you need any more convincing- @punchdenergy is all natural, low glycemic and gluten free-from raw, unprocessed green coffee beans, so they still contain much of the antioxidants that are normally burned off in the coffee roasting process.

Want fresh ginger juice but don’t like the cleanup of a traditional juicer? ( #or maybe don’t have a juicer?) I got you covered. This is the easiest hack, and most importantly to clean up takes about two seconds. are used to dread cleaning a juicer, and this makes everything so much faster. I’m a big fan of the French press for so many things but juicing fresh ginger is one of my all-time favorites. The best part? You don’t even have to peel the door and ginger just wash it lightly caught up in the smallest type pieces. Add as much water as you feel like adding, ( obviously the more water you add the less strong, the ginger juice will be, but that’s kind of the fun part as well ) then toss cut up ginger and water mixture into a blender or food processor and blend. Lastly, dump that mixture into a French press and Violia! Super fresh ginger juice ready for consumption on its own or to be tossed into your favorite morning wellness elixir 💕
